Illinois State Comptroller Judy Baar Topinka has passed away, and President Obama and First Lady Michelle Obama expressed their sadness and offered condolences to her family, friends, and constituents. Topinka had a long and notable career in Illinois politics, serving in the State Legislature and as Chair of the Illinois Republican Party. She was also the first woman to hold the position of State Treasurer. Known for her advocacy for her constituents, Topinka was described as blunt, pragmatic, cheerful, energetic, and willing to put politics aside to find practical solutions for the people of Illinois. Her passing is seen as a loss for the state.